(216, '2023-08-28 03:54:44', 2, 'services', 19, '{\"changed\":{\"description\":[\"<h1><b>Canadian Citizenship<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<p class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\"> Becoming a Canadian citizen will provide you with all the rights and privileges Canada has to offer\\u2013and there are many in terms of finances and mobility. If you already hold citizenship in another country, do not worry! Canada offers dual-citizenship so you will not need to forfeit your prior one. Core requirements include: <\\/p>\\r\\n<ul class=\\\\\\\"list\\\\\\\"><li>3 years of permanent residency<\\/li><li>Language proficiency in English or French<\\/li><li>No serious criminal offenses, and more<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<h4><b> Permanent Residence (PR) Card Renewal <\\/b><\\/h4>\\r\\n<p class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">A Permanent Resident (PR) Card is proof of your Canadian status and can be renewed to extend your PR upon expiration. You may be required to apply for a renewal if:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul class=\\\\\\\"list\\\\\\\"><li>PR card is expired or will expire in less than 9 months;<\\/li><li>You didn\\u2019t receive your PR card within 180 days of immigrating to Canada;<\\/li><li>PR card has been lost, stolen, or destroyed; or<\\/li><li>You legally changed your name<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<h4><b> Humanitarian & Compassionate (HC)<\\/b><\\/h4>\\r\\n<p class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">In special cases, you can apply for Permanent Resident (PR) status through Humanitarian & Compassionate (HC) if you have been living in Canada for at least 3 years with no status. This method of immigration is very circumstantial and requires substantial evidence supporting your reason to stay in Canada despite not qualifying through other immigration programs and may take several years to process. HC cases are generally granted if there are reasons to believe issues involving: <\\/p>\\r\\n<ul class=\\\\\\\"list\\\\\\\"><li>Families and or children<\\/li><li>Other substantial circumstantial evidence<\\/li><li>It indicates a high probability of undue harm to the applicant should he\\/she be moved back to their home country.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">In order to succeed in H&C cases, the candidate must typically demonstrate good behaviors in Canada such as employment background, community integration\\/involvement (ex. volunteering), & financial responsibility.<\\/p>\",\"<h1><b>Affidavit of Support for Canada Visa<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">When applying for a student visa in the Canada, one of the critical requirements is the Affidavit of Support.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nThis document serves as a promise from a sponsor or sponsor(s) to support the applicant during their stay in the country financially.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Affidavit of Support is a crucial document for student visa applicants, as it helps to demonstrate their ability to finance their education and living expenses while studying abroad.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\"]},\"moreInfo\":[]}'),
(217, '2023-08-28 03:55:04', 2, 'services', 19, '{\"changed\":{\"description\":[\"<h1><b>Affidavit of Support for Canada Visa<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">When applying for a student visa in the Canada, one of the critical requirements is the Affidavit of Support.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nThis document serves as a promise from a sponsor or sponsor(s) to support the applicant during their stay in the country financially.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Affidavit of Support is a crucial document for student visa applicants, as it helps to demonstrate their ability to finance their education and living expenses while studying abroad.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\",\"<h1><b>Affidavit of Support for Canada Visa<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">When applying for a student visa in the Canada, one of the critical requirements is the Affidavit of Support.\\r\\nThis document serves as a promise from a sponsor or sponsor(s) to support the applicant during their stay in the country financially.\\r\\nThe Affidavit of Support is a crucial document for student visa applicants, as it helps to demonstrate their ability to finance their education and living expenses while studying abroad.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\"]},\"moreInfo\":[]}'),
(218, '2023-08-28 04:04:59', 2, 'services', 19, '{\"changed\":{\"description\":[\"<h1><b>Affidavit of Support for Canada Visa<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">When applying for a student visa in the Canada, one of the critical requirements is the Affidavit of Support.\\r\\nThis document serves as a promise from a sponsor or sponsor(s) to support the applicant during their stay in the country financially.\\r\\nThe Affidavit of Support is a crucial document for student visa applicants, as it helps to demonstrate their ability to finance their education and living expenses while studying abroad.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\",\"<h1><b>Affidavit of Support for Canada Visa<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">The Affidavit of Support is a crucial requirement when requesting a student visa for Canada.\\r\\nThis document is a commitment from the sponsor or sponsors to provide the applicant with financial support while they are in the nation.\\r\\nThe Affidavit of Support is an important document for applicants of student visas since it shows their capacity to pay for their education and living costs while studying abroad.\\r\\n<h1 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\"><b>Requirements for Submitting an Affidavit of Support<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\nHere\\u2019s a list of the requirements for submitting an Affidavit of Support for Canada Student Visa\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Financial qualifications for the sponsor<\\/h5>The sponsor must demonstrate their ability to support the student for their studies financially. This includes providing proof of income, assets, and savings that meet or exceed the minimum income requirement set by the government.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Documents to be submitted by the sponsor<\\/h5>The sponsor must submit various financial papers, such as tax returns, bank statements, and employment letters, to support their claim of financial ability.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Information required for the Affidavit of Support<\\/h5>The Affidavit of Support form must be completed with accurate and complete information about the sponsor, including their full name, contact information, and relationship to the student.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Letter of Support and Intent<\\/h5>In this section of the affidavit, you should express your support for the student\\u2019s application and your intent to provide financial support for their education. This letter should include your relationship with the student and any other relevant information that supports your ability and willingness to provide financial support.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Submission deadlines<\\/h5>The Affidavit of Support must be submitted within the timeframe specified by the government or the educational institution. It is essential to check the specific deadline and ensure all necessary documentation is submitted on time.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\"]},\"moreInfo\":[]}'),
(219, '2023-08-28 04:08:57', 2, 'services', 19, '{\"changed\":{\"description\":[\"<h1><b>Affidavit of Support for Canada Visa<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">The Affidavit of Support is a crucial requirement when requesting a student visa for Canada.\\r\\nThis document is a commitment from the sponsor or sponsors to provide the applicant with financial support while they are in the nation.\\r\\nThe Affidavit of Support is an important document for applicants of student visas since it shows their capacity to pay for their education and living costs while studying abroad.\\r\\n<h1 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\"><b>Requirements for Submitting an Affidavit of Support<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\nHere\\u2019s a list of the requirements for submitting an Affidavit of Support for Canada Student Visa\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Financial qualifications for the sponsor<\\/h5>The sponsor must demonstrate their ability to support the student for their studies financially. This includes providing proof of income, assets, and savings that meet or exceed the minimum income requirement set by the government.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Documents to be submitted by the sponsor<\\/h5>The sponsor must submit various financial papers, such as tax returns, bank statements, and employment letters, to support their claim of financial ability.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Information required for the Affidavit of Support<\\/h5>The Affidavit of Support form must be completed with accurate and complete information about the sponsor, including their full name, contact information, and relationship to the student.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Letter of Support and Intent<\\/h5>In this section of the affidavit, you should express your support for the student\\u2019s application and your intent to provide financial support for their education. This letter should include your relationship with the student and any other relevant information that supports your ability and willingness to provide financial support.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Submission deadlines<\\/h5>The Affidavit of Support must be submitted within the timeframe specified by the government or the educational institution. It is essential to check the specific deadline and ensure all necessary documentation is submitted on time.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\",\"<h1><b>Affidavit of Support for Canada Visa<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">The Affidavit of Support is a crucial requirement when requesting a student visa for Canada.\\r\\nThis document is a commitment from the sponsor or sponsors to provide the applicant with financial support while they are in the nation.\\r\\nThe Affidavit of Support is an important document for applicants of student visas since it shows their capacity to pay for their education and living costs while studying abroad.\\r\\n<h1 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\"><b>Requirements for Submitting an Affidavit of Support<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\nHere\\u2019s a list of the requirements for submitting an Affidavit of Support for Canada Student Visa\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Financial qualifications for the sponsor<\\/h5>The sponsor must show that they have the financial resources to help the student with their study. Providing evidence of income, assets, and savings that meet or exceed the statutory minimum income level is a part of this.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Documents to be submitted by the sponsor<\\/h5>To prove their claim of financial capability, the sponsor must provide a variety of financial documents, including tax returns, bank statements, and job letters.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Information required for the Affidavit of Support<\\/h5>The sponsor\\\\\'s entire name, contact information, and relationship to the student must all be included on the Affidavit of Support form in exact and comprehensive detail.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Letter of Support and Intent<\\/h5>In this section of the affidavit, you should express your support for the student\\u2019s application and your intent to provide financial support for their education. This letter should include your relationship with the student and any other relevant information that supports your ability and willingness to provide financial support.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Submission deadlines<\\/h5>The Affidavit of Support must be submitted within the timeframe specified by the government or the educational institution. It is essential to check the specific deadline and ensure all necessary documentation is submitted on time.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\"]},\"moreInfo\":[]}'),
(220, '2023-08-28 04:20:05', 2, 'services', 19, '{\"changed\":{\"description\":[\"<h1><b>Affidavit of Support for Canada Visa<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">The Affidavit of Support is a crucial requirement when requesting a student visa for Canada.\\r\\nThis document is a commitment from the sponsor or sponsors to provide the applicant with financial support while they are in the nation.\\r\\nThe Affidavit of Support is an important document for applicants of student visas since it shows their capacity to pay for their education and living costs while studying abroad.\\r\\n<h1 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\"><b>Requirements for Submitting an Affidavit of Support<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\nHere\\u2019s a list of the requirements for submitting an Affidavit of Support for Canada Student Visa\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Financial qualifications for the sponsor<\\/h5>The sponsor must show that they have the financial resources to help the student with their study. Providing evidence of income, assets, and savings that meet or exceed the statutory minimum income level is a part of this.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Documents to be submitted by the sponsor<\\/h5>To prove their claim of financial capability, the sponsor must provide a variety of financial documents, including tax returns, bank statements, and job letters.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Information required for the Affidavit of Support<\\/h5>The sponsor\\\\\'s entire name, contact information, and relationship to the student must all be included on the Affidavit of Support form in exact and comprehensive detail.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Letter of Support and Intent<\\/h5>In this section of the affidavit, you should express your support for the student\\u2019s application and your intent to provide financial support for their education. This letter should include your relationship with the student and any other relevant information that supports your ability and willingness to provide financial support.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Submission deadlines<\\/h5>The Affidavit of Support must be submitted within the timeframe specified by the government or the educational institution. It is essential to check the specific deadline and ensure all necessary documentation is submitted on time.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\",\"<h1><b>Affidavit of Support for Canada Visa<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">The Affidavit of Support is a crucial requirement when requesting a student visa for Canada.\\r\\nThis document is a commitment from the sponsor or sponsors to provide the applicant with financial support while they are in the nation.\\r\\nThe Affidavit of Support is an important document for applicants of student visas since it shows their capacity to pay for their education and living costs while studying abroad.\\r\\n<h1 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\"><b>Requirements for Submitting an Affidavit of Support<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\nHere\\u2019s a list of the requirements for submitting an Affidavit of Support for Canada Student Visa\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Financial qualifications for the sponsor<\\/h5>The sponsor must show that they have the financial resources to help the student with their study. Providing evidence of income, assets, and savings that meet or exceed the statutory minimum income level is a part of this.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Documents to be submitted by the sponsor<\\/h5>To prove their claim of financial capability, the sponsor must provide a variety of financial documents, including tax returns, bank statements, and job letters.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Information required for the Affidavit of Support<\\/h5>The sponsor\\\\\'s entire name, contact information, and relationship to the student must all be included on the Affidavit of Support form in exact and comprehensive detail.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Letter of Support and Intent<\\/h5>In this section of the affidavit, you should express your support for the student\\u2019s application and your intent to provide financial support for their education. This letter should include your relationship with the student and any other relevant information that supports your ability and willingness to provide financial support.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Submission deadlines<\\/h5>The Affidavit of Support must be submitted within the timeframe specified by the government or the educational institution. It is essential to check the specific deadline and ensure all necessary documentation is submitted on time.\\r\\n<h1 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\"><b>How to Write an Affidavit of Support Letter<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\nWriting an Affidavit of Support letter can be daunting, but it can be quickly done with the proper guidelines.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Gather information<\\/h5>The first step is to gather all the information required to write the Affidavit of Support. This includes personal details of the sponsor and the student, financial information, and the purpose of the support.\\r\\nBegin the letter: Start by addressing the letter to the appropriate authority, such as the embassy or consulate, and include the date and subject of the letter.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Introduce yourself<\\/h5>Begin by introducing yourself as the sponsor and include your full name, address, and relationship to the student.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">State your financial ability<\\/h5>State your financial ability to support the student throughout their studies. This includes providing details of your current employment, salary, and other income sources.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Include a letter of support and intent<\\/h5>Write a letter stating your commitment to providing financial support to the student and indicating that you understand the financial responsibilities associated with sponsoring a student.\\r\\n<h5 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\">Provide notarization and certification<\\/h5>Getting the Affidavit of Support notarized and certified by a legal authority must make it a legally binding document.\\r\\n<\\/div>\"]},\"moreInfo\":[]}'),
(221, '2023-08-28 04:35:57', 2, 'services', 20, '{\"changed\":{\"description\":[\"<h1><b>Canadian Citizenship<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<p class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\"> Becoming a Canadian citizen will provide you with all the rights and privileges Canada has to offer\\u2013and there are many in terms of finances and mobility. If you already hold citizenship in another country, do not worry! Canada offers dual-citizenship so you will not need to forfeit your prior one. Core requirements include: <\\/p>\\r\\n<ul class=\\\\\\\"list\\\\\\\"><li>3 years of permanent residency<\\/li><li>Language proficiency in English or French<\\/li><li>No serious criminal offenses, and more<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<h4><b> Permanent Residence (PR) Card Renewal <\\/b><\\/h4>\\r\\n<p class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">A Permanent Resident (PR) Card is proof of your Canadian status and can be renewed to extend your PR upon expiration. You may be required to apply for a renewal if:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul class=\\\\\\\"list\\\\\\\"><li>PR card is expired or will expire in less than 9 months;<\\/li><li>You didn\\u2019t receive your PR card within 180 days of immigrating to Canada;<\\/li><li>PR card has been lost, stolen, or destroyed; or<\\/li><li>You legally changed your name<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<h4><b> Humanitarian & Compassionate (HC)<\\/b><\\/h4>\\r\\n<p class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">In special cases, you can apply for Permanent Resident (PR) status through Humanitarian & Compassionate (HC) if you have been living in Canada for at least 3 years with no status. This method of immigration is very circumstantial and requires substantial evidence supporting your reason to stay in Canada despite not qualifying through other immigration programs and may take several years to process. HC cases are generally granted if there are reasons to believe issues involving: <\\/p>\\r\\n<ul class=\\\\\\\"list\\\\\\\"><li>Families and or children<\\/li><li>Other substantial circumstantial evidence<\\/li><li>It indicates a high probability of undue harm to the applicant should he\\/she be moved back to their home country.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">In order to succeed in H&C cases, the candidate must typically demonstrate good behaviors in Canada such as employment background, community integration\\/involvement (ex. volunteering), & financial responsibility.<\\/p>\",\"<h1><b>Submit your Advance Declaration<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">You can make your customs and immigration declaration using Advance Declaration in the ArriveCAN app before you fly into one of Canada\\\\\'s participating airports. Upon arrival:\\r\\nconfirm (certify) your declaration at a kiosk or eGate \\u2013 it\\\\\'s 30% faster, take advantage of Advance Declaration express lanes\\r\\n<h1 class=\\\\\\\"text-dark mt-3\\\\\\\"><b>How to submit your Advance Declaration<\\/b><\\/h1>\\r\\nFollowing these four steps:\\r\\n<ul class=\\\\\\\"list\\\\\\\"><li>Sign in to the ArriveCAN app or the web version online and follow the prompts<\\/li><li>Confirm your travel identity document information (passport or Canadian permanent resident card)<\\/li><li>Answer the customs and immigration questions truthfully<\\/li><li>Submit the declaration 72 hours prior to arriving in Canada<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/div>\"]},\"moreInfo\":[]}'),
