ctor that is signed. Your face, however, must not be obscured in any manner.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Dimension and Size (Pixel)<\\/td><td>Not specified.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Attire, clothing, dress code<\\/td><td>Wear whatever you like.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Beard<\\/td><td>There are no limitations.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Quality<\\/td><td>The picture must be printed on glossy, high-quality photo paper. Additionally, the flash must not distort the image.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Lighting<\\/td><td>The conditions have to be ideal enough to produce a sharp image. Additionally, you must be able to see yourself in the picture.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Digital Alternations<\\/td><td>No, images that have been digitally manipulated of any form won\\\\\'t be allowed. Even removing a red eye from a photo is not permitted.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Hair<\\/td><td>Either wearing your hair up or down is acceptable.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Commercial Photographer<\\/td><td>If a professional photographer is submitting your photos, they must include their name, address, and signature on the back of both images.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Comments<\\/td><td>You must write the following information on the back of one of your photos: the applicant\\\\\'s name, the address of the picture studio, the date the photo was taken, the statement \\\\\\\"I certify this to be a true likeness of (applicant)\\\\\\\" and a sign (guarantor\\\\\'s name and surname). However, if you are renewing a passport for an adult, you can exclude the guarantor\\\\\'s details and simply include the applicant\\\\\'s name, the location of the photo studio, and the date the photo was taken. Additionally, the photographer has the option of using a stamp or handwriting the studio address and date.<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Quantity needed for application<\\/td><td>2<\\/td><\\/tr><\\/table >\\r\\n<\\/div>\"]},\"moreInfo\":[]}');
