(551, '2024-02-05 02:05:03', 1, 'services', 22, '{\"changed\":{\"name\":[\"Tax Lawyer\",\"Divorce Law\"],\"uri_value\":[\"tax-lawyer\",\"divorce-law\"],\"short_description\":[\"Tax lawyers provide legal advice and assistance to individuals, businesses, and organizations to help them navigate the intricacies of tax regulations and ensure compliance with the law.\",\"Divorce Lawyer in Ontario<\\/h1><h2 style=\\\\\\\"font-family: var(--fnt-t-3-ff); font-size: calc(var(--fnt-t-3-s) * var(--fnt-t-3-s-mtp)); line-height: var(--fnt-t-3-lh); font-weight: var(--fnt-t-3-w); margin-top: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-cnt-m); color: var(--lt-fnt-tc-2); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\">Bringing Clarity to Your Divorce in Ontario<\\/h2>\"],\"description\":[\"<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">\\r\\nTax Lawyer is a legal professional who specializes in tax law. Tax lawyers are experts in the intricate and ever-changing field of taxation, and they provide legal advice and representation to individuals, businesses, and organizations in matters related to taxes. Their role extends beyond traditional accounting services, as they primarily focus on the legal aspects of taxation, including tax planning, etc.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nA tax lawyer is often an attorney whose practice is concentrated on tax matters such as the Goods and Services Tax (GST), Retail Sales Tax (RST\\/PST), Personal or Corporate Income Tax, Harmonized Sales Tax (HST), and the Ontario Employer Health Tax (EHT).\\r\\n\\r\\nA tax attorney frequently represents clients in front of numerous governmental bodies (audits, objections, and appeals). A large number of these attorneys will also represent clients in Canadian Tax Court appeals.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhile some tax lawyers specialize in a range of tax sectors, others could only concentrate on one tax category. A tax lawyer will typically know more about tax law than a regular practitioner.\\r\\n\\r\\nNumerous tax attorneys at Simple Accounting & Tax Solutions Inc.\\u00a0are knowledgeable in all of these fields and are available to represent you before the Canada Revenue Agency (CRA) and other government agencies. For any tax-related issues, the tax attorneys at Simple Accounting & Tax Solutions Inc.\\u00a0can also defend you before the Tax Court of Canada, the Federal Court of Appeal, and the Supreme Court of Canada.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe ability to handle all of our non-resident clients\\\\\' Canadian tax and trade issues in one sitting, with just one of our partners, is something we believe gives us a competitive advantage. All of Simple Accounting & Tax Solutions Inc.\\\\\'s tax lawyers are also knowledgeable in other areas of our practice, such as customs and trade-related matters.\\r\\n<\\/div>\",\"<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\"><h1 style=\\\\\\\"font-family: var(--fnt-t-1-ff); font-size: calc(var(--fnt-t-1-s) * var(--fnt-t-1-s-mtp)); letter-spacing: var(--fnt-t-1-ls); line-height: var(--fnt-t-1-lh); font-weight: var(--fnt-t-1-w); word-break: break-word; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\">Divorce Lawyer in Ontario<\\/h1><h2 style=\\\\\\\"font-family: var(--fnt-t-3-ff); font-size: calc(var(--fnt-t-3-s) * var(--fnt-t-3-s-mtp)); line-height: var(--fnt-t-3-lh); font-weight: var(--fnt-t-3-w); margin-top: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-cnt-m); color: var(--lt-fnt-tc-2); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\">Bringing Clarity to Your Divorce in Ontario<\\/h2><p style=\\\\\\\"transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><font color=\\\\\\\"#343434\\\\\\\" face=\\\\\\\"Poppins, sans-serif\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 16.3629px;\\\\\\\">The procedure by which a couple can end their legal marriage is governed by the Divorce Act, R.S.C. 1985, c. 3.<\\/span><\\/font><\\/p><p style=\\\\\\\"transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 16.3629px; color: rgb(52, 52, 52); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\\\\\\\">For couples who want to end their relationship, getting a divorce is not a must; instead, they might decide to split up and sign a separation agreement. It is only required if one of the parties decides to get married again, in which case the other party has to obtain a formal separation decree from the court along with a final certificate attesting to it.<\\/span><br><\\/p><p style=\\\\\\\"transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><font color=\\\\\\\"#343434\\\\\\\" face=\\\\\\\"Poppins, sans-serif\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 16.3629px;\\\\\\\">Our Ontario divorce lawyers at Jahedul Law can help you with this procedure. We gladly cater to the entirety of Ontario.<\\/span><\\/font><\\/p><h3 style=\\\\\\\"font-family: var(--fnt-t-3-ff); font-size: calc(var(--fnt-t-3-s) * var(--fnt-t-3-s-mtp)); line-height: var(--fnt-t-3-lh); font-weight: var(--fnt-t-3-w); margin-top: var(--g-cnt-cnt-ttl-m); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-cnt-m); margin-left: 0px; color: var(--lt-fnt-tc-3); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><strong style=\\\\\\\"transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\">Application for Divorce in Canada<\\/strong><\\/h3><p style=\\\\\\\"color: rgb(52, 52, 52); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 16.3629px; transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\">Section 8(1) of the Act permits either spouse, or both, to file for divorce when a pair has a \\\\\\\"breakdown of their marriage.\\\\\\\" This application could be submitted to:<\\/p><ul style=\\\\\\\"list-style: none; padding: 0px; margin: 1em 0px; color: rgb(52, 52, 52); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 16.3629px; transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><li style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-itm-lh); position: relative; padding: 0.1em 0px 0.1em 1.5em; transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\">The Superior Court of Justice, or<\\/li><li style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-itm