(555, '2024-02-05 02:23:07', 1, 'services', 31, '{\"changed\":{\"name\":[\"Corporate Tax Advice & Planning\",\"Wills & Estates Law\"],\"uri_value\":[\"corporate-tax-advice-and-planning\",\"wills-and-estates-law\"],\"description\":[\"<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">\\r\\nCorporate Tax Advice & Planning refers to the specialized services provided by tax professionals to help businesses navigate the complex landscape of corporate taxation. This aspect of accounting and tax services focuses on developing strategies to optimize a company\\\\\'s tax position while ensuring compliance with relevant tax laws and regulations. <br>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4><b> CORPORATE TAX ADVICE & PLANNING <\\/b><\\/h4>\\r\\nOur Corporate Tax Advice group offers a comprehensive range of tax advisory services for all types of clients, from multinational public corporations to regional entrepreneurial enterprises.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe service all sectors of the economy including telecommunications, mining, real estate development, and manufacturing through a diversified and highly experienced team of dedicated tax advisors.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe provide sophisticated yet practical solutions to the unique challenges faced by business entities and their respective owners. Our corporate advisory services encompass all aspects of tax-related business planning, including corporate reorganizations and consolidations, mergers and acquisitions, divestitures, structured finance, and tax-driven transactions. Examined together with executive remuneration, shareholder taxation, and corporate governance ramifications, we provide a fully integrated approach to corporate taxation planning, whether transactional, operational, or structural.\\r\\n\\r\\nOur advice extends beyond Canada as part of our broad cross-border and international tax planning practice. We routinely assist clients located in various and varied foreign jurisdictions who are investing or otherwise carrying on business in Canada, as well as Canadian-based businesses with operations abroad. We possess both the knowledge and experience to address all aspects of Canadian tax planning for business enterprises.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\",\"<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\\\\\"text-color\\\\\\\"><h1 style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-t-1-lh); word-break: break-word; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\\\">Laws pertaining to wills and estates govern the transfer of property from one person to another as well as any associated events.<\\/span><\\/h1><h1 style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-t-1-lh); word-break: break-word; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 14px; color: inherit; font-family: inherit;\\\\\\\">It covers intestate succession, heir succession rights, and testamentary validity of wills. The responsibilities of an administrator or executor are also covered by the legislation.<\\/span><\\/h1><h1 style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-t-1-lh); word-break: break-word; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\\\">Province-specific estate and will laws<\\/span><\\/h1><h1 style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-t-1-lh); word-break: break-word; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 14px;\\\\\\\">There isn\\\\\'t a single federal statute in Canada that governs estates and wills. Rather, the various provinces or territories pass wills and estates legislation.<\\/span><\\/h1><h1 style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-t-1-lh); word-break: break-word; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 14px; color: inherit; font-family: inherit;\\\\\\\">Put another way, provincial and territory governments oversee wills and estates laws in Canada, which also include powers of attorney, probate, guardianship, and trusteeship.<\\/span><br><\\/h1><h1 style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-t-1-lh); word-break: break-word; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 14px; color: inherit; font-family: inherit;\\\\\\\">The following are a few examples of wills and estates legislation found in the nation\\\\\'s common law provinces:<\\/span><\\/h1><h1 style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-t-1-lh); word-break: break-word; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><ul style=\\\\\\\"margin-bottom: 40px; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 33px; font-size: 22px;\\\\\\\"><li><span style=\\\\\\\"font-weight: bolder;\\\\\\\">Ontario:<\\/span>&nbsp;Succession Law Reform Act (<a href=\\\\\\\"#\\\\\\\" target=\\\\\\\"_blank\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\"color: rgb(58, 168, 204);\\\\\\\">SLRA<\\/a>) and&nbsp;<a href=\\\\\\\"#\\\\\\\" target=\\\\\\\"_blank\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\"color: rgb(58, 168, 204);\\\\\\\">Estates Act<\\/a><\\/li><li><span style=\\\\\\\"font-weight: bolder;\\\\\\\">British Columbia:&nbsp;<\\/span>Wills, Estates and Succession Act (<a href=\\\\\\\"#\\\\\\\" target=\\\\\\\"_blank\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\"color: rgb(58, 168, 204);\\\\\\\">WESA<\\/a>)<\\/li><li><span style=\\\\\\\"font-weight: bolder;\\\\\\\">Alberta:<\\/span>&nbsp;Wills and Succession Act (<a href=\\\\\\\"#\\\\\\\" target=\\\\\\\"_blank\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\"color: rgb(58, 168, 204);\\\\\\\">WSA<\\/a>)<\\/li><li><span style=\\\\\\\"font-weight: bolder;\\\\\\\">Nova Scotia:<\\/span>&nbsp;<a href=\\\\\\\"#\\\\\\\" target=\\\\\\\"_blank\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\"color: rgb(58, 168, 204);\\\\\\\">Wills Act<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\\\\\"#\\\\\\\" target=\\\\\\\"_blank\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\"color: rgb(58, 168, 204);\\\\\\\">Probate Act<\\/a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\\\\\\\"#\\\\\\\" target=\\\\\\\"_blank\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\"color: rgb(58, 168, 204);\\\\\\\">Intestate Succession Act<\\/a><\\/li><\\/ul><br><\\/h1><h1 style=\\\\\\\"line-height: var(--fnt-t-1-lh); word-break: break-word; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: var(--g-cnt-ttl-ttl-m); transition: none 0s ease 0s !important;\\\\\\\"><span style=\\\\\\\"font-size: 14px; color: inherit; font-family: inherit;\\\\\\\"><\\/span><br><\\/h1><\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/div>\"]},\"moreInfo\":[]}'),
